item.title: CVE-2023-28577|2024-04-12T16:24:20.201Z -- qualcomm%2C%20inc. -- snapdragon
item.description: In the function call related to CAM_REQ_MGR_RELEASE_BUF there is no check if the buffer is being used. So when a function called cam_mem_get_cpu_buf to get the kernel va to use, another thread can call CAM_REQ_MGR_RELEASE_BUF to unmap the kernel va which cause UAF of the kernel address.

item.title: CVE-2023-28576|2024-04-12T16:24:16.350Z -- qualcomm%2C%20inc. -- snapdragon
item.description: The buffer obtained from kernel APIs such as cam_mem_get_cpu_buf() may be readable/writable in userspace after kernel accesses it. In other words, user mode may race and modify the packet header (e.g. header.count), causing checks (e.g. size checks) in kernel code to be invalid. This may lead to out-of-bounds read/write issues.
